headline: Here's Why Shares in UPS Are Lower Today
summary: Shares in package delivery giant UPS (NYSE: UPS) were down 3.4% in trading before 10 a.m. this morning.  The decline was in sympathy with a larger decline at peer FedEx (NYSE: FDX) after the release of its fiscal third-quarter 2025 earnings.  Unfortunately, FedEx did not have good news for UPS.

headline: FedEx Stock Drops After Cut to Outlook
summary: Shares in FedEx sank Friday, after the package-shipping company cut its annual forecasts for sales and earnings.    FedEx stock recently stood nearly 11% lower at $219.21.   That put the shares on pace for their lowest close since June 1, 2023, according to Dow Jones Market Data.
